  "verdict": "8 real control sequences (4 aftershock cascades from USGS ComCat incl. Landers/Tohoku/Ridgecrest; 4 solar-flare sequences after large X-flares, NGDC GOES XRS), 4 clear the >= 2.8-period gate. Kernel omega=2.583 false-positive rate: frozen 0/4 (Wilson95 [0.0, 0.4899]), strict 0/4. the detector is QUIET at the kernel on every gated control (FP 0/4, Wilson95 upper 0.4899), consistent with the nominal ~5% threshold rate -> the existing TFPT-channel nulls are SPECIFIC: the kernel frequency does not fire on generic Omori/DSI-type cascades. CONTROL 1 (Efimov ladder, exactly-derived non-TFPT DSI lambda=e^(pi/s0)=22.69): measured cold-atom ratios (Cs/7Li/39K) combine to 21.331+-1.12 \u2014 Efimov-consistent (-1.22 sigma) and 8.88 sigma from the TFPT lambda=11.39 (Cs alone 7.39 sigma); the frozen detector on the gated Efimov comb fired at the kernel 0/25 seeds while detecting omega_Efimov=2.01 at 100% -> PASSED. CONTROL 2 (glass/MCT exponent spread, structural): gamma across 7 systems spans [2.2, 2.8] (std 0.2023, 4.0x the median per-system error) \u2014 the TFPT bend 2.7095 sits inside the spread but a LOCKED universal bend is rejected at chi2=43.36/7 dof (~4.87 sigma): boundary-less two-step relaxation shows no frozen bend -> PASSED. COMBINED over all 5 gated DSI controls (4 gated cascade sequences + Efimov ladder (EF.02)): kernel fired 0/5 (Wilson95 [0.0, 0.4345]). FIREWALL: controls have no TFPT mapping by construction; this calibrates detector specificity only and is NOT evidence for TFPT. No claim; nothing [E]."
